{"id": "duc04-testb-23:3#9", "contents": "U.S. aid to Brazil would clearly send a symbolic message: that after a year of trying to manage the financial crisis through the monetary fund, the United States is now ready to put a limited amount of its own capital at risk to prevent further havoc \u2013 not only for Brazil but to stop chaos spreading to Argentina, Mexico, and other countries that are major U.S. trading partners. This would be a change of strategy, as the United States has operated almost entirely through international financial institutions, chiefly the IMF. However, it would also be a risky move for President Clinton, economically and politically."}
